The paper focuses on the development of an Android app that tracks smartphone data and utilizes psychometric personality questionnaires. The paper also introduces a general context data model consisting of four categories that focus on the user's different types of interactions with the smartphone and a privacy model specifically for apps related to the collection of mobile data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), followed by Cybersecurity and Privacy (cs.CY), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), and Multimedia (cs.MM).
